cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper focuses on the secure and economic operation of the power system, which involves control and optimization of charging load of EVs. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper proposes incentive mechanisms and pricing schemes to encourage optimal charging behavior, which involves computational modeling and optimization. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although not explicitly mentioned, the paper may involve machine learning techniques for predicting EV charging demand and optimizing charging schedules. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Similar to cs.LG, the paper may involve AI techniques for optimizing charging schedules and predicting EV charging demand. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper evaluates the efficacy of the proposed optimal charging models and incentive mechanisms through simulated tests, which involves performance evaluation.
